This object is a dictionary (`dict`) with a single key (`"subs"`) and its value is also a dictionary, which contains two nested dictionaries. There is no list (`list`) in this structure. The top level object does not contain any other key-value pairs besides `"id"` and `"Z"`.

To provide an excerpt as they appear in the YAML file, separated by `\n\n`, the content would be:

```
This will break up the indented YAML structure into multiple lines, separated by two newlines (`\n\n`). However, note that indentation is very important in YAML, and changing the indentation might render the YAML structure invalid. It is best to stick to the indentation used in the original YAML file.
